{
  "stem": "14552.4",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, you were telling us about your experiences in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[SIGHS] The eeriness of those lights at-- all night, and when I had to go to use the facilities, that, that unbelievable strangeness of the lights, the electric wires, the fences, and the men with the-- with the guns in the lookout, and the, the people who couldn't take it anymore and flung themselves against the electric fence-- it's there always.",
      "word_count": 61
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It is a picture you can not take out from your memory.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And there are times when I look at night-- if I get up and I go to the window and I look out, I have this mixture of feelings looking on Rutledge Road under light and seeing, in the back of my mind, Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[CRYING] [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] It's, it's something-- and then the morning, to discuss with everybody who it was that did that.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the fear of-- and the hopelessness and helplessness has, has embedded itself very, very deeply.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then every single day that renewed attrition, punishment, imprinting the mind with fear, and seeing that people who are not feeling well taken to the infirmary, never to be seen again.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "When I was-- I had pneumonia.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they smuggled out aspirins from the infirmary because my-- the friends, my sister-- they would never permit me to go to the infirmary.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they-- and they-- and I, I just don't understand with being as, as frail as I was-- because I just was a skinny child-- and having pneumonia and fainting regularly, and I'm here.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I say, well, this is-- this is something that is very difficult to explain.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "How did I get through this?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And-- How do you explain it?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I, I just-- I just think that explanations are not good enough.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
